-Will! Will!
-Come on. Mom. We're almost there.

12
00:00:39.581 --> 00:00:42.167
-You're so fast. I can't keep up.
-Mom. there it is.

13
00:00:42.251 --> 00:00:45.045
-You need to be in the Olympics.
-Let's go. Mom. We're so close.

14
00:00:45.128 --> 00:00:48.048
Thank you for taking me to see
Jett's new billboard.

15
00:00:48.131 --> 00:00:51.802
-Jett's huge!
-Will. say "cheese."

16
00:00:51.885 --> 00:00:53.136
Will for three.

17
00:00:54.012 --> 00:00:55.973
Okay. boy. don't be doing all of that now.

18
00:00:56.056 --> 00:00:58.517
All right. Guess it's time to go.

19
00:00:58.600 --> 00:01:00.978
You have to go to work. right?

20
00:01:01.061 --> 00:01:02.688
One second. Wait. turn it around.

21
00:01:02.771 --> 00:01:04.690
I got it! There we go. Okay.

22
00:01:04.772 --> 00:01:06.942
How about you and I

23
00:01:07.025 --> 00:01:10.612
watch the Thorns from inside the stadium?

24
00:01:10.696 --> 00:01:12.823
'Cause I'm taking my baby

25
00:01:12.906 --> 00:01:17.578
to see his very first. yep. roarball game!

26
00:01:18.912 --> 00:01:19.746
What?

27
00:01:21.874 --> 00:01:22.875
Is this for real?

28
00:01:22.958 --> 00:01:24.960
I mean. unless you're busy?

29
00:01:25.502 --> 00:01:27.171
Oh. baby.

30
00:01:27.254 --> 00:01:29.173
-It's okay.
-Thank you.

31
00:01:29.256 --> 00:01:32.426
Thank you so much. I love you. Mom.

32
00:01:32.509 --> 00:01:34.344
I love you too. Will.

33
00:01:34.428 --> 00:01:36.847
-Let's go. Mom. Come on. Roots run deep.
-Yeah. let's go!

34
00:01:37.431 --> 00:01:39.516
It's right here. Right here. Come on.

35
00:01:39.600 --> 00:01:41.268
Mom. stop it.

36
00:01:41.852 --> 00:01:43.395
Let's go!

37
00:01:43.478 --> 00:01:44.521
Let's go!

38
00:01:44.605 --> 00:01:46.398
Welcome to the Greenhouse!

39
00:01:46.481 --> 00:01:47.733
It's starting!

40
00:01:51.195 --> 00:01:54.615
Are you ready?

41
00:01:56.491 --> 00:01:58.368
-Who is the GOAT?
-Who is the GOAT?

42
00:01:58.452 --> 00:01:59.870
-So. who's the GOAT?
-Who's the GOAT?

43
00:01:59.953 --> 00:02:02.497
Who is truly the GOAT?

44
00:02:12.049 --> 00:02:14.635
Introducing Vineland's very own.

45
00:02:14.718 --> 00:02:18.972
the hometown hero. a five-time all-star.

46
00:02:19.056 --> 00:02:20.682
Jett Fillmore.

47
00:02:20.766 --> 00:02:23.143
Yeah! Let's go. Vineland.

48
00:02:23.227 --> 00:02:25.604
Let's go. Jett!

49
00:02:26.897 --> 00:02:29.066
Having a good time. Will? Baby?

50
00:02:32.694 --> 00:02:34.363
That's gonna be me. Mom.

51
00:02:35.239 --> 00:02:36.406
When I get big.

52
00:02:37.157 --> 00:02:39.284
I'm gonna be just like her.

53
00:02:55.843 --> 00:02:57.010
One... Yeah!

54
00:02:57.094 --> 00:02:59.429
It's the power of the mind.
Your body's not tired.

55
00:02:59.513 --> 00:03:01.473
You can take a break. Don't take a break.

56
00:03:05.435 --> 00:03:06.436
You got this.

57
00:03:07.771 --> 00:03:09.022
Keep pushing.

58
00:03:09.106 --> 00:03:10.732
Keep pushing.

59
00:03:13.318 --> 00:03:14.152
I'm okay!

60
00:03:15.028 --> 00:03:16.655
Hey. Will. Are you working out?

61
00:03:16.738 --> 00:03:18.323
Hey. Theo. You know it.

62
00:03:18.407 --> 00:03:21.451
Jett Fillmore doesn't take a day off.
and neither do I.

63
00:03:21.535 --> 00:03:24.538
My dad said you can't play roarball
'cause you're too small.

64
00:03:25.247 --> 00:03:26.915
Everyone says that. Theo.

65
00:03:26.999 --> 00:03:31.003
When I'm on the Thorns.
you'll be courtside. my bro-dent.

66
00:03:31.086 --> 00:03:32.254
Heck. yeah.

67
00:03:32.337 --> 00:03:33.380
Go. Thorns!

68
00:03:35.883 --> 00:03:37.301
No rest for the ballers.

69
00:03:42.014 --> 00:03:43.849
Hey! Will!

70
00:03:44.349 --> 00:03:47.352
I hope you're not trying to sneak out

71
00:03:48.020 --> 00:03:50.272
without paying your rent.

72
00:03:51.315 --> 00:03:52.482
Yeah.

73
00:03:52.566 --> 00:03:55.944
I'll get it to you as soon as you
fix those holes in the ceiling.

74
00:03:56.028 --> 00:03:57.863
What holes?

75
00:03:57.946 --> 00:04:00.199
Gotta go to work. Catch you later. Frank.

76
00:04:00.282 --> 00:04:01.700
Will!

77
00:04:03.368 --> 00:04:05.037
Good morning. Vineland!

78
00:04:05.120 --> 00:04:07.080
Whoever said that. be quiet. please.

79
00:04:10.667 --> 00:04:11.793
Roots run deep!

80
00:04:11.877 --> 00:04:13.712
Roots run deep!

81
00:04:13.795 --> 00:04:14.880
Welcome back.

82
00:04:14.963 --> 00:04:17.216
Tonight. it's Jett Fillmore. the vet.

83
00:04:17.298 --> 00:04:19.927
taking on Mane Attraction. the champ.

84
00:04:20.010 --> 00:04:22.221
The GOAT debate starts here.

85
00:04:22.304 --> 00:04:23.889
Thorns versus Magma.

86
00:04:23.972 --> 00:04:25.140
Go Magma!

87
00:04:25.224 --> 00:04:26.433
Go Shivers!

88
00:04:26.517 --> 00:04:29.269
Yeah. go whoever is playing the Thorns.
I don't care.

89
00:04:29.353 --> 00:04:30.604
Gerald!

90
00:04:30.687 --> 00:04:34.149
I'm gonna kick you out if you keep wearing
the other teams' jerseys.

91
00:04:34.233 --> 00:04:35.567
Carol. I'm the ultimate hater.

92
00:04:35.651 --> 00:04:36.818
No pie for you.

93
00:04:36.902 --> 00:04:38.153
Sheep. She took my pie.

94
00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:41.740
The Thorns have broken his heart
one too many times.

95
00:04:41.823 --> 00:04:43.534
This is Vineland. Gerald.

96
00:04:43.617 --> 00:04:46.161
We never give up. We've always got hope.

97
00:04:46.245 --> 00:04:49.373
The Thorns. they just need
to draft your boy.

98
00:04:49.456 --> 00:04:51.416
I'll turn things around real quick.

99
00:04:51.500 --> 00:04:52.960
So. they're drafting delivery goats now?

100
00:04:54.002 --> 00:04:55.671
I need one to deliver food.

101
00:04:55.754 --> 00:04:58.590
About that. Ms Carol. can I get a raise?

102
00:04:58.674 --> 00:04:59.883
You want a raise?

103
00:04:59.967 --> 00:05:04.012
Tell the Thorns to win a few games
so we can get the crowds back in here.

104
00:05:04.096 --> 00:05:08.058
I remember when Jett was a rookie.
This place used to be full.

105
00:05:08.141 --> 00:05:10.435
Before we realised
she was never gonna win us a Claw?

106
00:05:10.519 --> 00:05:12.145
Carol. can I have my pie back. please?

107
00:05:12.229 --> 00:05:15.065
Keep talking.
I'll cut you off from ice cream too.

108
00:05:15.148 --> 00:05:17.734
-Be careful with these.
-Got it.

109
00:05:18.652 --> 00:05:20.070
Moe needs more coffee.

110
00:05:20.153 --> 00:05:22.239
and the out-of-towners.
they want their cheque.

111
00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:24.867
How do you always do that?
Freaks me out every time.

112
00:05:24.950 --> 00:05:27.244
Hey. I'm a goat. I see everything.

113
00:05:31.039 --> 00:05:32.374
-Pass it. Will.
-Okay!

114
00:05:32.457 --> 00:05:34.626
-Hey. guys.
-Got it! See you later. Will!

115
00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:36.920
Thorns are already down by 20.

116
00:05:37.004 --> 00:05:38.005
Come on.

117
00:05:38.088 --> 00:05:39.089
Up here.

118
00:05:40.215 --> 00:05:41.633
All right. Let's do this.

119
00:05:45.971 --> 00:05:47.556
-Thank you.
-I got you.

120
00:06:06.200 --> 00:06:07.826
Step back. Yes!

121
00:06:08.952 --> 00:06:10.662
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

122
00:06:10.746 --> 00:06:12.247
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

123
00:06:12.748 --> 00:06:14.583
-Here you go.
-Appreciate you.

124
00:06:19.880 --> 00:06:21.757
My mammal. Finally. bro.

125
00:06:21.840 --> 00:06:23.800
Chill. Daryl. You ordered a water.

126
00:06:23.884 --> 00:06:25.886
Water is food too. bro.

127
00:06:25.969 --> 00:06:27.221
So. Hannah. how's Jett doing?

128
00:06:27.304 --> 00:06:29.431
Mane's kind of working Jett tonight.

129
00:06:29.515 --> 00:06:32.392
I hate to say it. she might be washed.

130
00:06:32.476 --> 00:06:35.187
You serious? Jett can handle
that one-trick pony.

131
00:06:35.270 --> 00:06:38.190
Is his one trick
being the best at roarball?

132
00:06:38.273 --> 00:06:40.275
He's got the shooting. the passing...

133
00:06:40.359 --> 00:06:41.610
Picture-perfect pecs.

134
00:06:41.693 --> 00:06:43.654
Luxurious locks.

135
00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:44.947
Mane is pretty much him.

136
00:06:46.823 --> 00:06:47.950
Oh. my!

137
00:06:48.033 --> 00:06:49.660
-Mane Attraction just put...
-On her head!

138
00:06:49.743 --> 00:06:51.370
...the former number-one pick.
Olivia Burke...

139
00:06:51.453 --> 00:06:53.205
-That's not good.
-...on a poster.

140
00:06:54.039 --> 00:06:54.915
No way.

141
00:06:55.582 --> 00:06:57.084
There's already memes?

142
00:06:57.167 --> 00:06:59.378
"Poster child"? Now. that's rough.

143
00:06:59.461 --> 00:07:01.338
Yeah. that was so not cool.

144
00:07:02.297 --> 00:07:04.758
All right. I'm out.
I'm gonna go train at the Cage.

145
00:07:04.842 --> 00:07:07.219
What? You're not gonna
watch the game with us?

146
00:07:07.302 --> 00:07:09.513
Nah. I gotta go while the Cage is empty.

147
00:07:09.596 --> 00:07:11.765
'cause after the game.
you know it's gonna fill up.

148
00:07:11.849 --> 00:07:14.434
Do not let Grizz catch you.

149
00:07:14.518 --> 00:07:15.519
I won't.

150
00:07:16.228 --> 00:07:19.439
Roots run deep. Roots run deep.

151
00:07:19.523 --> 00:07:20.774
Roots run deep.

152
00:07:36.874 --> 00:07:38.250
Step back. Jett!

153
00:07:40.043 --> 00:07:42.546
The crowd goes wild.

154
00:08:05.110 --> 00:08:06.111
Another one.

155
00:08:07.571 --> 00:08:10.699
With only five seconds left.
the ball goes to Harris.

156
00:08:10.782 --> 00:08:12.159
He's all alone.

157
00:08:12.242 --> 00:08:14.953
Three. two. one...

158
00:08:21.126 --> 00:08:22.753
What's going on here. folks?

159
00:08:22.836 --> 00:08:24.129
They're resetting the clock?

160
00:08:24.213 --> 00:08:25.339
Don't question it.

161
00:08:25.422 --> 00:08:27.257
He's got time for one more shot.

162
00:08:27.341 --> 00:08:29.843
Three. two. one...

163
00:08:38.227 --> 00:08:42.481
Roots run deep. Roots run deep.
Roots run deep.

164
00:08:42.563 --> 00:08:43.899
Roots run deep.

165
00:08:43.982 --> 00:08:46.318
One day. baby. One day.

166
00:08:53.450 --> 00:08:55.327
Get that weak sauce up out of here.

167
00:08:55.410 --> 00:08:57.621
Yo. what's your problem. Grizz?

168
00:08:57.704 --> 00:08:59.581
Every day you're here.

169
00:08:59.665 --> 00:09:02.084
Every day I gotta kick you out.

170
00:09:02.167 --> 00:09:04.044
I mean. what are the rules. y'all?

171
00:09:04.127 --> 00:09:06.129
Smalls can't ball.

172
00:09:06.213 --> 00:09:08.549
First off. I'm not a small. I'm a medium.

173
00:09:08.632 --> 00:09:10.592
What? Medium fries?

174
00:09:10.676 --> 00:09:13.136
You will never make it into Roar.

175
00:09:13.220 --> 00:09:15.180
I mean. come on. Let me run.

176
00:09:15.264 --> 00:09:17.140
I'm better than half of y'all anyways.

177
00:09:17.224 --> 00:09:18.767
Let me show you what I got.

178
00:09:19.560 --> 00:09:20.561
Ball me.

179
00:09:21.061 --> 00:09:23.730
Only thing you're running
is off this court.

180
00:09:24.898 --> 00:09:26.358
Now get out of here.

181
00:09:26.984 --> 00:09:27.985
Whatever.

182
00:09:28.068 --> 00:09:30.445
Goodnight. Shirley.
You're in my house now.

183
00:09:32.114 --> 00:09:34.825
And that's the game. Thorns lose by 26.

184
00:09:34.908 --> 00:09:36.577
Clock's ticking. Jett.

185
00:09:36.660 --> 00:09:39.872
Jett. Jett. Jett.
hey. can you sign this for me?

186
00:09:39.955 --> 00:09:42.833
Of course. Anything for a fan.

187
00:09:42.916 --> 00:09:43.917
There you go. kid.

188
00:09:44.001 --> 00:09:45.294
Thanks. Jett.

189
00:09:46.086 --> 00:09:47.754
Why can't you win a championship?

190
00:09:48.672 --> 00:09:50.090
Retire already!

191
00:09:50.174 --> 00:09:51.341
Jett. could we take a photo?

192
00:09:51.425 --> 00:09:52.843
Jett. third loss in a row.

193
00:09:52.926 --> 00:09:54.887
-How does it feel?
-Flo? Where's Flo?

194
00:09:54.970 --> 00:09:56.471
-When are we gonna stop sucking?
-Flo!

195
00:09:56.555 --> 00:09:57.848
Hey. Flo?

196
00:09:57.931 --> 00:09:59.099
Who's seen Flo?

197
00:10:11.111 --> 00:10:12.946
Hey. there. grumpy cat.

198
00:10:15.824 --> 00:10:17.743
How'd the game end?

199
00:10:17.826 --> 00:10:21.538
I stopped watching and punched myself
in the face instead.

200
00:10:22.080 --> 00:10:23.916
You think this is funny?

201
00:10:23.999 --> 00:10:25.876
You're the team owner. Flo.

202
00:10:25.959 --> 00:10:27.503
How am I supposed to win

203
00:10:27.586 --> 00:10:30.672
when you've got me surrounded
by head cases and has-beens?

204
00:10:30.756 --> 00:10:32.257
Hey. I'm working on it.

205
00:10:32.341 --> 00:10:35.177
We don't even have a sixth player. Flo.
but you got your hooves done.

206
00:10:35.260 --> 00:10:39.181
Listen here. Jett.
free agents aren't free. Okay?

207
00:10:39.264 --> 00:10:41.767
So unless you have a sixth player in mind

208
00:10:41.850 --> 00:10:45.562
who can fill an arena
and doesn't want a big. fat cheque.

209
00:10:45.646 --> 00:10:48.565
I'm gonna get back to my mud bath. okay?

210
00:10:48.649 --> 00:10:50.192
That is hogwash.

211
00:10:50.275 --> 00:10:52.110
It's your job to figure it out.

212
00:10:52.194 --> 00:10:53.570
Trade players. sell the team...

213
00:10:53.654 --> 00:10:57.449
I don't care what you got to do.
Just do it. Now.

214
00:10:57.533 --> 00:11:00.619
Careful what you wish for. Jett.

215
00:11:05.958 --> 00:11:07.000
He's fine.

216
00:11:24.393 --> 00:11:27.312
Hey. I'm driving here.
Get out of the road. you medium.

217
00:11:27.396 --> 00:11:29.189
Keep it down. Why are you so loud?

218
00:11:32.776 --> 00:11:34.736
Hello. William.

219
00:11:34.820 --> 00:11:36.655
Hey. Frank. How are you?

220
00:11:36.738 --> 00:11:40.200
Would you happen to have that rent?

221
00:11:40.784 --> 00:11:42.828
Yeah. yeah. Right. Right.

222
00:11:42.911 --> 00:11:45.163
Frank. I got you. It's all right here.

223
00:11:45.247 --> 00:11:47.666
-I meant to give it to you today actually.
-22. 23...

224
00:11:47.749 --> 00:11:50.836
This is not actual money.
this piece of paper.

225
00:11:50.919 --> 00:11:52.045
Yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah.

226
00:11:52.129 --> 00:11:54.381
What about last month's
and the month before?

227
00:11:54.423 --> 00:11:57.384
Frank. it's me. Come on.

228
00:11:57.467 --> 00:12:00.429
I just need a little more time.

229
00:12:00.512 --> 00:12:02.639
You had time. Will.

230
00:12:03.348 --> 00:12:05.017
I got mouths to feed.

231
00:12:05.100 --> 00:12:06.852
I don't need one more.

232
00:12:06.935 --> 00:12:07.853
-Hey. Will.
-Hey. Will.

233
00:12:07.936 --> 00:12:09.396
-Hey. Will.
-Hey. Will.

234
00:12:09.479 --> 00:12:12.107
-Hey. guys.
-Hey. Will. Hey. Will.

235
00:12:12.191 --> 00:12:14.151
Hey. Will. Hey. Will. Hey. Will.

236
00:12:14.234 --> 00:12:15.235
Y'all are still awake?

237
00:12:15.319 --> 00:12:17.112
-Hey. Will.
-What's up. Theo?

238
00:12:17.196 --> 00:12:18.906
Did they let you play at the Cage today?

239
00:12:18.989 --> 00:12:20.490
You know me. I'm working on it.

240
00:12:20.574 --> 00:12:21.700
That's a lot of kids.

241
00:12:21.783 --> 00:12:23.202
Indeed it is.

242
00:12:23.285 --> 00:12:24.536
I'm sorry. kiddo.

243
00:12:24.620 --> 00:12:27.414
Look. get me my rent money by tomorrow

244
00:12:27.497 --> 00:12:29.875
or I gotta rent the room to somebody else.

245
00:12:29.958 --> 00:12:31.126
Capisce?

246
00:12:31.210 --> 00:12:33.504
-Will. I forgot to tell you--
-Hey. kids. come on. Get in the tub.

247
00:12:33.587 --> 00:12:34.588
Here we go. here we go.

248
00:12:42.721 --> 00:12:43.722
Whatever.

249
00:12:45.557 --> 00:12:46.558
You need money?

250
00:12:46.642 --> 00:12:50.312
Well. you're in luck 'cause you can start
earning up to 300 bucks per day.

251
00:12:50.395 --> 00:12:54.775
How? By trading crypto
on BigBroncoCrypto...

252
00:12:55.275 --> 00:12:58.237
Frank. I'm pregnant again.

253
00:12:58.320 --> 00:13:01.073
That's amazing. sweetheart.

254
00:13:02.074 --> 00:13:05.118
You know. we needed another one of those.

255
00:13:05.661 --> 00:13:06.703
Hey. Will.

256
00:13:07.204 --> 00:13:09.122
gonna need that rent money.

257
00:13:33.605 --> 00:13:36.024
Boom! Check these out.

258
00:13:36.108 --> 00:13:39.319
Vineland green. Fillmore Fours.
in the flesh.

259
00:13:39.403 --> 00:13:41.405
Jett wore these in the Furball game.

260
00:13:41.488 --> 00:13:43.657
Normally. these sell for around six.

261
00:13:43.740 --> 00:13:46.577
but I'll give it to you

262
00:13:46.660 --> 00:13:47.661
for five.

263
00:13:47.744 --> 00:13:50.330
No. not the Fours.

264
00:13:50.914 --> 00:13:52.207
I wanted those.

265
00:13:52.291 --> 00:13:53.667
But you're broke.

266
00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:56.503
But if I had the Fours I wouldn't look it.

267
00:13:56.587 --> 00:13:59.173
Yes. Yes. you would. It's gonna be okay.

268
00:13:59.256 --> 00:14:02.176
Pristine upper mesh. Taut laces.

269
00:14:03.927 --> 00:14:05.762
-Nutty.
-Nasty.

270
00:14:05.846 --> 00:14:06.763
250.

271
00:14:06.847 --> 00:14:08.849
-Come on.
-250? How dare you.

272
00:14:08.932 --> 00:14:10.559
The disrespect.

273
00:14:10.642 --> 00:14:12.936
Come on. Will. I can do instalments.

274
00:14:13.020 --> 00:14:16.148
Yeah. yeah. that's great. Daryl.
but my landlord can't.

275
00:14:16.773 --> 00:14:17.900
Okay.

276
00:14:17.983 --> 00:14:19.902
I can't watch this.

277
00:14:19.985 --> 00:14:22.070
So. 400?

278
00:14:22.613 --> 00:14:24.031
-240.
-It's going down?

279
00:14:24.114 --> 00:14:26.617
-230.
-Dang. stop! Please. please!

280
00:14:26.700 --> 00:14:29.536
-Yo! Y'all are not gonna believe this.
-No way!

281
00:14:29.620 --> 00:14:33.874
Mane is at the Cage.
and he's taking on all challengers.

282
00:14:35.751 --> 00:14:40.005
So. we doing this or what?

283
00:14:40.547 --> 00:14:41.381
Okay. fine.

284
00:14:41.965 --> 00:14:43.008
All right. Let's dip.

285
00:14:55.562 --> 00:14:56.480
Who's got next?

286
00:15:00.108 --> 00:15:01.235
Now watch this.

287
00:15:01.902 --> 00:15:03.028
Give me that.

288
00:15:05.155 --> 00:15:05.989
Garbage.

289
00:15:07.157 --> 00:15:10.077
I said. who's got next?

290
00:15:10.160 --> 00:15:12.621
I can't hear nothing. Where y'all at?

291
00:15:13.455 --> 00:15:15.415
Who got next?

292
00:15:15.499 --> 00:15:16.708
Hey. yo. Check ball.

293
00:15:17.584 --> 00:15:18.752
Yeah!

294
00:15:18.836 --> 00:15:20.379
Get him. Grizz!

295
00:15:20.462 --> 00:15:23.131
Got a piece of flaming garbage over here.

296
00:15:24.550 --> 00:15:26.009
Touch me. Touch me.

297
00:15:35.143 --> 00:15:36.436
Yeah!

298
00:15:36.520 --> 00:15:38.188
Get lost. Mane. you're a bum.

299
00:15:38.272 --> 00:15:41.650
Seriously? You mean to tell me
this is the best Vineland's got?

300
00:15:41.733 --> 00:15:44.403
I thought the Cage
is where roarball was born.

301
00:15:44.945 --> 00:15:49.575
I guess this town's only as weak
as its greatest player.

302
00:15:49.658 --> 00:15:51.243
Hey. where she at?

303
00:15:51.326 --> 00:15:55.998
If Jett's nowhere to be found.
then somebody gotta answer me.

304
00:15:56.081 --> 00:15:58.041
-Who's got next?
-I got next.

305
00:15:58.125 --> 00:15:59.334
Who said that?

306
00:15:59.418 --> 00:16:00.502
Hey!

307
00:16:00.586 --> 00:16:03.797
Nobody talks about Jett and Vineland
like that.

308
00:16:03.881 --> 00:16:06.592
Excuse me. Pardon. Hey. move out the way.

309
00:16:06.675 --> 00:16:07.676
I got next.

310
00:16:08.552 --> 00:16:09.761
Check up.

311
00:16:09.845 --> 00:16:11.471
Wait. wait. a goat?

312
00:16:14.391 --> 00:16:15.851
Thank you for the laugh. little dude.

313
00:16:15.934 --> 00:16:19.229
but why don't you just run on back
to the kiddie pool or something.

314
00:16:19.313 --> 00:16:20.439
Get you an ice cream.

315
00:16:20.522 --> 00:16:22.566
But. seriously. any takers?

316
00:16:23.192 --> 00:16:24.693
Even if I put money on it?

317
00:16:24.776 --> 00:16:26.486
First the shoes. now your rent money?

318
00:16:26.570 --> 00:16:28.488
Yes. Will. Commit.

319
00:16:28.572 --> 00:16:30.157
Mane. what are you gonna do now?

320
00:16:30.240 --> 00:16:31.950
Where's all the big talk now. Mane?

321
00:16:32.034 --> 00:16:33.535
Let's go. Vineland!

322
00:16:34.161 --> 00:16:38.498
So this is all the great Vineland
has to offer?

323
00:16:38.582 --> 00:16:41.084
A goat and some spare change?

324
00:16:42.085 --> 00:16:43.212
But you know what?

325
00:16:43.295 --> 00:16:46.006
Mane doesn't duck smoke so check up.

326
00:16:46.089 --> 00:16:47.341
Let's do it.

327
00:16:48.342 --> 00:16:50.385
Everything counts as one.

328
00:16:50.886 --> 00:16:51.929
First to three.

329
00:16:52.721 --> 00:16:53.639
Your ball.

330
00:17:01.271 --> 00:17:02.022
Oh. snap!

331
00:17:02.105 --> 00:17:03.106
That's one.

332
00:17:03.732 --> 00:17:04.983
I'd fight a big for that.

333
00:17:08.237 --> 00:17:10.196
So you do know how to pass.

334
00:17:10.280 --> 00:17:12.199
You gonna guard me
from all the way out there?

335
00:17:13.450 --> 00:17:14.742
Let's go.

336
00:17:15.285 --> 00:17:16.203
Come on.

337
00:17:19.248 --> 00:17:21.083
When I get that ball. it's over.

338
00:17:31.760 --> 00:17:33.637
You got owned by a goat!

339
00:17:34.221 --> 00:17:36.098
-Oh. shoot!
-Hey!

340
00:17:36.181 --> 00:17:37.474
This goat out here!

341
00:17:39.852 --> 00:17:41.937
This dude's eating beans!

342
00:17:48.277 --> 00:17:50.237
All right. Let's get serious.

343
00:17:50.320 --> 00:17:53.031
Looks like you're gonna make me
take my chains off.

344
00:17:53.115 --> 00:17:55.158
Yeah. man. Take it all off.

345
00:17:56.910 --> 00:17:58.120
Okay. I see.

346
00:17:58.203 --> 00:18:00.455
You're an outside shooter. huh?

347
00:18:01.248 --> 00:18:02.416
Now get past me.

348
00:18:06.587 --> 00:18:07.921
Now we playing for real.

349
00:18:08.005 --> 00:18:09.548
This is how it feel in the league.

350
00:18:10.174 --> 00:18:11.258
This is my house.

351
00:18:16.638 --> 00:18:18.098
You're mine now.

352
00:18:21.435 --> 00:18:22.811
Boom!

353
00:18:25.189 --> 00:18:26.398
Boom shakalaka!

354
00:18:39.077 --> 00:18:40.621
Fool. I wasn't helping you up.

355
00:18:41.538 --> 00:18:43.248
I just wanted my cash.

356
00:18:43.874 --> 00:18:45.209
Thanks.

357
00:18:47.044 --> 00:18:50.214
Hey! We got goat money.

358
00:18:50.297 --> 00:18:51.423
That wasn't bad.

359
00:18:51.465 --> 00:18:54.676
Everyone didn't have their phones
out for that long.

360
00:18:54.760 --> 00:18:55.844
Right. Daryl?

361
00:18:55.928 --> 00:18:57.888
Yes. they did.

362
00:19:14.279 --> 00:19:15.614
Come on. Come on.

363
00:19:25.832 --> 00:19:26.834
What?

364
00:19:30.420 --> 00:19:31.547
I respect that.

365
00:19:31.630 --> 00:19:35.884
Hey. Will. Will. I'm really sorry
about my dad.

366
00:19:35.968 --> 00:19:39.680
But I want you to know I believe in you.

367
00:19:41.014 --> 00:19:43.141
And I made you a sandwich. Catch!

368
00:19:47.479 --> 00:19:49.439
Oops. Airball.

369
00:19:49.523 --> 00:19:50.524
Sorry about that.

370
00:19:52.442 --> 00:19:53.694
Don't even worry about it.

371
00:19:53.777 --> 00:19:56.947
I'll still see you at the Greenhouse
when you're playing for the Thorns!

372
00:19:57.030 --> 00:19:58.657
-Thanks. Theo.
-Good luck!

373
00:20:00.909 --> 00:20:06.123
-Yo. I told you that video was crazy.
-Yeah. that dude was guzzling.

374
00:20:06.206 --> 00:20:08.917
-Yo! What's up. my mammal?
-Hey.

375
00:20:09.001 --> 00:20:10.210
-Hey.
-There he is.

376
00:20:10.294 --> 00:20:13.005
Thanks for letting me crash at your place.

377
00:20:13.088 --> 00:20:15.716
You brought your stuff?
Hey. throw it on the pile.

378
00:20:15.799 --> 00:20:17.050
Still haven't cleaned.

379
00:20:17.134 --> 00:20:19.094
Okay. just pick a pile.
They're all filthy.

380
00:20:19.178 --> 00:20:22.389
Now quit your yapping and come check out
what I've been cooking up.

381
00:20:39.072 --> 00:20:40.407
You like that?

382
00:20:40.490 --> 00:20:42.492
Come on. this is gonna go viral.

383
00:20:42.576 --> 00:20:44.077
You broke his ankles.

384
00:20:44.161 --> 00:20:45.704
Yeah. and he broke my horn.

385
00:20:46.205 --> 00:20:49.917
Will. look. you wanted footage
of you playing against bigs.

386
00:20:50.000 --> 00:20:53.545
And you just went up against the biggest.
baddest in all of roarball.

387
00:20:53.629 --> 00:20:55.714
-Yep. yep. Facts.
-You did that. Will.

388
00:20:56.548 --> 00:20:58.300
Okay.

389
00:20:58.383 --> 00:21:02.471
Well. I'm just gonna make this one live
'cause I think Daryl just farted.

390
00:21:02.554 --> 00:21:03.680
I'll see you both later.

391
00:21:03.764 --> 00:21:05.807
I got a date. Need to shave.

392
00:21:05.891 --> 00:21:07.142
With who?

393
00:21:07.226 --> 00:21:09.019
I didn't tell you? Your mom.

394
00:21:09.770 --> 00:21:11.188
Oh. shoot.

395
00:21:11.271 --> 00:21:12.356
Yeah. she got you. bro.

396
00:21:12.439 --> 00:21:15.150
Okay. okay. Wasn't even funny.

397
00:21:15.234 --> 00:21:18.403
Hey. bro. Wanna play some Roar 2K?

398
00:21:18.487 --> 00:21:19.738
Nah. think I'm good.

399
00:21:19.821 --> 00:21:20.989
Should probably call it a night. you know?

400
00:21:21.073 --> 00:21:23.033
No. sure thing.
Yeah. make yourself comfortable.

401
00:21:23.575 --> 00:21:25.160
I'm gonna get on these sticks.

402
00:21:29.957 --> 00:21:30.958
Hello!

403
00:21:33.293 --> 00:21:34.545
Okay.

404
00:21:59.778 --> 00:22:01.029
It's him. look.

405
00:22:01.697 --> 00:22:03.782
Look. it's totally him!

406
00:22:06.910 --> 00:22:08.579
Hey! What's up. buddy?

407
00:22:09.913 --> 00:22:10.914
Hey. Will.

408
00:22:10.998 --> 00:22:13.250
-Hey. Will.
-Hi. anonymous animal.

409
00:22:13.333 --> 00:22:15.043
Look. Mom. It's Will.

410
00:22:15.127 --> 00:22:17.588
-I'm sorry.
-That's okay. It's okay.

411
00:22:22.759 --> 00:22:26.555
Yo. who is the clown
that parked like that outside?

412
00:22:27.806 --> 00:22:28.932
Everybody good?

413
00:22:30.976 --> 00:22:32.144
Why are y'all not blinking?

414
00:22:32.227 --> 00:22:35.189
That's me. sweetheart. I'm the clown.

415
00:22:35.272 --> 00:22:38.483
You're Florence Everson!
You're the owner of the Thorns!

416
00:22:38.567 --> 00:22:41.904
You can ignore all the voice mails.
Mr Harris.

417
00:22:41.987 --> 00:22:44.323
It looks like I found you myself.

418
00:22:44.406 --> 00:22:46.158
She's been waiting for you.

419
00:22:46.241 --> 00:22:48.160
Without ordering anything.

420
00:22:48.660 --> 00:22:49.703
Sit.

421
00:22:49.786 --> 00:22:52.331
You had quite the game yesterday.

422
00:22:52.414 --> 00:22:56.084
You broke Mane's ankles so hard. I thought
they were gonna have to put him down!

423
00:22:56.168 --> 00:22:59.129
And the Internet just loved it.

424
00:22:59.713 --> 00:23:01.798
They love you.

425
00:23:01.882 --> 00:23:04.092
Yo! That's crazy!

426
00:23:04.635 --> 00:23:05.928
It gets crazier.

427
00:23:06.011 --> 00:23:09.431
Will. maybe you haven't noticed.
but the team is awful.

428
00:23:09.515 --> 00:23:10.516
Oh. no. We trash.

429
00:23:10.599 --> 00:23:15.479
We have the league's best player
and no path to the Claw. again...

430
00:23:15.562 --> 00:23:16.980
Small to small.

431
00:23:17.064 --> 00:23:22.903
I believe you are exactly what Jett
and this team needs right now.

432
00:23:22.986 --> 00:23:28.450
Goat. sure. But I think you might be
a two-horned unicorn.

433
00:23:28.534 --> 00:23:30.160
-Really?
-Yeah.

434
00:23:30.244 --> 00:23:33.080
I'd like to make you an offer.

435
00:23:33.580 --> 00:23:37.793
We need a sixth player to join the Thorns
for the back half of the season.

436
00:23:38.502 --> 00:23:42.005
Oh. my gosh. Is it really--
Is it finally happening?

437
00:23:42.089 --> 00:23:44.633
I just need you to sign here.
some initials here.

438
00:23:44.716 --> 00:23:46.468
and you're officially a Thorn.

439
00:23:46.552 --> 00:23:48.804
And Jett. She signed off on this?

440
00:23:48.887 --> 00:23:51.056
In many ways. it was her idea.

441
00:23:51.139 --> 00:23:52.683
Yeah. So what's it gonna be?

442
00:23:52.766 --> 00:23:54.643
Play for Vineland.

443
00:23:54.726 --> 00:23:57.396
or stay here and bus my table?

444
00:23:57.479 --> 00:24:00.107
Pen. Pen! Pen. Someone give me a pen!

445
00:24:00.190 --> 00:24:01.358
I don't have a--

446
00:24:02.150 --> 00:24:03.277
Thank you.

447
00:24:04.903 --> 00:24:07.114
W. H.

448
00:24:07.197 --> 00:24:09.783
Where there's a Will. there's a way.

449
00:24:09.867 --> 00:24:14.288
Congratulations. sweetie.
We're so proud of you.

450
00:24:14.371 --> 00:24:16.623
Will! Will! Will! Will! Will!

451
00:24:18.208 --> 00:24:19.459
I cannot believe it!

452
00:24:19.543 --> 00:24:21.670
I'm gonna be a Vineland Thorn!

453
00:24:21.753 --> 00:24:24.548
-Breaking news! Will. it went viral!
-You're not gonna believe it!

454
00:24:24.631 --> 00:24:25.716
It certainly did.

455
00:24:25.799 --> 00:24:27.384
I'm so excited. Will.

456
00:24:27.467 --> 00:24:28.844
Who's the fancy pig?

457
00:24:29.803 --> 00:24:31.889
I hate this town.

458
00:24:51.575 --> 00:24:53.535
It hurts. It hurts.

459
00:24:59.166 --> 00:25:01.084
Welcome to the Roar Round-up.

460
00:25:01.168 --> 00:25:03.086
I'm two-time champion. Chuck.

461
00:25:03.170 --> 00:25:06.089
alongside my co-host.
itty-bitty-bitey-buddy.

462
00:25:06.173 --> 00:25:07.508
-Rusty.
-Rusty!

463
00:25:07.591 --> 00:25:10.427
I can't wait till they put you
out to pasture. Chuck.

464
00:25:10.928 --> 00:25:14.515
That's good. Well. but back to
the question we ask every season.

465
00:25:14.598 --> 00:25:16.934
Can you be the GOAT
without winning a championship?

466
00:25:17.017 --> 00:25:19.436
-Yes. What is that?
-Let's face it. Claws make careers.

467
00:25:19.520 --> 00:25:20.646
-You don't say!
-Nuh-uh.

468
00:25:20.729 --> 00:25:22.814
I feel for Fillmore.
She's always been a great player.

469
00:25:22.898 --> 00:25:25.025
but Father Time catches up with everyone.

470
00:25:25.108 --> 00:25:27.444
Without me. they wouldn't
have anything to talk about.

471
00:25:27.528 --> 00:25:29.154
All stats. no Claws.

472
00:25:29.238 --> 00:25:30.906
But you can't put all the blame on her.

473
00:25:30.989 --> 00:25:34.326
Anyone who's watched this team and thinks
Jett's the biggest problem is blind as a--

474
00:25:34.409 --> 00:25:37.788
Blind as a what. Chuck? Say it.
Blind as a what?

475
00:25:37.871 --> 00:25:41.500
I am the all-time leading scorer
in Roar history.

476
00:25:41.583 --> 00:25:44.920
Speaking of the Thorns.
we've got some breaking news. Chuck!

477
00:25:45.003 --> 00:25:46.922
The Vineland Thorns have finally
signed a sixth player.

478
00:25:47.005 --> 00:25:48.799
Looks like they're finally
getting Jett some help.

479
00:25:48.882 --> 00:25:50.092
Yes! A crocodile?

480
00:25:50.175 --> 00:25:52.094
No. no. no. no. Bigger. A gorilla?

481
00:25:52.177 --> 00:25:54.054
-We go now to owner Florence Everson...
-That's what I'm talking about.

482
00:25:54.137 --> 00:25:55.472
...with an exclusive interview.

483
00:25:55.556 --> 00:25:58.267
We signed roarball's first small.

484
00:25:58.350 --> 00:25:59.768
A small what?

485
00:25:59.852 --> 00:26:01.478
We got a little...

486
00:26:01.562 --> 00:26:02.521
A little what?

487
00:26:02.604 --> 00:26:04.273
-...teeny...
-A what now?

488
00:26:04.356 --> 00:26:05.732
-...tiny...
-Come again.

489
00:26:05.816 --> 00:26:06.859
...goat.

490
00:26:07.860 --> 00:26:09.403
A goat?

491
00:26:25.961 --> 00:26:27.254
Not again.

492
00:26:27.337 --> 00:26:29.173
Florence Marjorie Everson!

493
00:26:29.256 --> 00:26:33.051
You're signing a goat?
Have you lost your mind?

494
00:26:33.135 --> 00:26:35.345
Okay. Excuse me.

495
00:26:35.429 --> 00:26:38.432
You're the one who asked for a team
who could win the Claw

496
00:26:38.515 --> 00:26:41.059
and you didn't care how. Remember?

497
00:26:41.143 --> 00:26:43.228
Well. I care about this.

498
00:26:43.312 --> 00:26:45.022
I can't play with a goat.

499
00:26:45.105 --> 00:26:46.982
He's an embarrassment to the team.

500
00:26:47.065 --> 00:26:49.151
He's an embarrassment to the city.
He's a--

501
00:26:49.234 --> 00:26:50.652
He's sitting right there.

502
00:26:52.112 --> 00:26:53.739
Hey!

503
00:26:55.490 --> 00:26:56.950
You gotta be kidding me.

504
00:26:57.034 --> 00:26:59.077
I couldn't even see him in the chair. Flo.

505
00:26:59.161 --> 00:27:00.662
How am I supposed to see him on the court?

506
00:27:00.746 --> 00:27:02.998
I'll be the goat in the Thorns jersey.

507
00:27:03.081 --> 00:27:04.082
You feel me?

508
00:27:04.166 --> 00:27:05.167
Uh-huh.

509
00:27:05.667 --> 00:27:07.377
Look away. Flo. I'm just gonna eat him.

510
00:27:07.503 --> 00:27:10.506
Yeah. I'm gonna eat him
with a side of ranch dressing.

511
00:27:10.589 --> 00:27:13.133
and we're gonna act like
none of this happened.

512
00:27:13.217 --> 00:27:14.635
I do not taste good.

513
00:27:14.718 --> 00:27:16.053
I thought you said she knew.

514
00:27:16.136 --> 00:27:18.472
It's my job to bend the truth. Will.
Come on.

515
00:27:19.515 --> 00:27:23.018
It's also my job to play the long game.

516
00:27:23.101 --> 00:27:26.605
This is generating more attention
than we have had in years.

517
00:27:26.688 --> 00:27:28.941
You don't want him on the court.
that's your call.

518
00:27:29.024 --> 00:27:31.443
But he stays on the roster.

519
00:27:32.110 --> 00:27:34.071
You must have lost your mind.

520
00:27:34.154 --> 00:27:35.989
Put your paw down.

521
00:27:36.823 --> 00:27:38.617
You should be elated.

522
00:27:38.700 --> 00:27:43.580
The stars have aligned perfectly
because the press is dying to meet Will.

523
00:27:43.664 --> 00:27:45.374
Will. down. Get down.

524
00:27:45.457 --> 00:27:47.751
-Okay.
-And I want you to introduce him.

525
00:27:47.835 --> 00:27:49.878
-No. Not happening.
-Yes. you are.

526
00:27:49.962 --> 00:27:52.548
They're actually waiting for you
right downstairs.

527
00:27:52.631 --> 00:27:54.842
So keep them tails up high. yes?

528
00:27:54.925 --> 00:27:58.011
Big smiles! Love you both! Now get out!

529
00:28:00.931 --> 00:28:02.474
Jett. hey.

530
00:28:02.558 --> 00:28:05.853
I just wanted you to know.
this is my dream come true.

531
00:28:05.936 --> 00:28:09.064
I mean. to play with you. like.
my favourite player of all time.

532
00:28:09.606 --> 00:28:11.358
I know I'm not what you expected.

533
00:28:11.441 --> 00:28:14.278
but I've spent my whole life
training for this moment.

534
00:28:14.361 --> 00:28:15.946
And if you just give me a sho--

535
00:28:16.029 --> 00:28:19.533
Look. kid. I saw your little viral video.

536
00:28:19.616 --> 00:28:21.702
Mane baked you like a birthday cake.

537
00:28:21.785 --> 00:28:25.122
Yeah. yeah. no. I'm gonna enjoy
watching the piranhas eat you alive.

538
00:28:25.205 --> 00:28:26.248
Jett! Jett!

539
00:28:26.331 --> 00:28:28.834
-Jett! Over here! Jett!
-Hey. Jett! Over here!

540
00:28:28.917 --> 00:28:30.252
-Will! Will!
-Will. over here!

541
00:28:30.335 --> 00:28:31.753
-Will!
-Will. over here!

542
00:28:31.837 --> 00:28:34.214
-Will. over here!
-Will. Will. Will!

543
00:28:50.981 --> 00:28:52.941
Let's get started.
Hardest questions first.

544
00:28:53.025 --> 00:28:54.985
Do you think going viral
in a playground entitles you

545
00:28:55.068 --> 00:28:56.278
to play professional roarball?

546
00:28:56.361 --> 00:28:57.529
Do you worry you'll let other smalls down?

547
00:28:57.613 --> 00:28:59.156
Aren't you just
a shameless publicity stunt

548
00:28:59.239 --> 00:29:01.074
to distract from another
Thorns losing season?

549
00:29:01.158 --> 00:29:02.159
Are you actually a goat?

550
00:29:02.242 --> 00:29:03.785
-Don't you just kinda suck?
-I...

551
00:29:03.869 --> 00:29:05.871
Sorry. Can you repeat the question?

552
00:29:05.954 --> 00:29:08.373
Hey. hey. One at a time. y'all.

553
00:29:08.457 --> 00:29:10.959
This boy is not even media trained. okay?

554
00:29:11.043 --> 00:29:13.253
So. Will. How does it feel
to be the first small ever

555
00:29:13.337 --> 00:29:15.047
to sign a professional roarball contract?

556
00:29:15.672 --> 00:29:18.675
To be honest with you.
it's all kinda surreal.

557
00:29:18.759 --> 00:29:21.803
I mean. last night I was fighting off
roaches at my best friend's crib.

558
00:29:21.887 --> 00:29:24.389
and now I'm playing for the Thorns.

559
00:29:24.932 --> 00:29:26.266
You shouldn't have said that.

560
00:29:26.350 --> 00:29:28.477
Will. we are getting word that
the roach community was pretty offended

561
00:29:28.560 --> 00:29:29.561
by your last comment.

562
00:29:29.645 --> 00:29:30.938
Would you care to issue an apology?

563
00:29:31.021 --> 00:29:33.190
Oh. gosh. No. no. no. no.
That's not what I meant.

564
00:29:33.273 --> 00:29:35.484
-I love roaches.
-Lies.

565
00:29:35.567 --> 00:29:37.486
-Can we move on to the next question?
-Up here.

566
00:29:37.569 --> 00:29:40.113
So. Will. you're not at all concerned
about being hurt?

567
00:29:40.197 --> 00:29:42.199
Roarball takes its toll on
the toughest of bigs.

568
00:29:42.282 --> 00:29:45.118
I imagine for a small. it could be fatal.

569
00:29:45.661 --> 00:29:48.205
-Well...
-No. no. Will knows the risks.

570
00:29:48.288 --> 00:29:50.582
Could he be clobbered? Possibly.

571
00:29:50.666 --> 00:29:52.209
Crushed? Perhaps.

572
00:29:52.292 --> 00:29:54.169
Killed? Probably.

573
00:29:54.253 --> 00:29:56.672
But that's how much he loves the game.

574
00:29:56.755 --> 00:29:58.382
He'd die for it.

575
00:29:59.007 --> 00:30:01.301
-Right. Will?
-Right.

576
00:30:01.385 --> 00:30:02.469
What about Mane?

577
00:30:02.553 --> 00:30:04.346
Are you worried about a rematch
down the line?

578
00:30:04.429 --> 00:30:05.430
No. No way.

579
00:30:05.514 --> 00:30:09.726
We call this dude the horse whisperer.
'cause he broke that bronco's back. okay?

580
00:30:09.810 --> 00:30:11.353
You know what he was telling me earlier?

581
00:30:11.436 --> 00:30:12.980
He's got a nickname for Mane.

582
00:30:13.063 --> 00:30:15.399
He calls him "My Little Pony."

583
00:30:15.941 --> 00:30:17.442
-Don't you?
-No. I didn't say that.

584
00:30:17.526 --> 00:30:18.694
-You do.
-I did not say that.

585
00:30:18.777 --> 00:30:22.281
And he also said that Mane
definitely ain't the GOAT.

586
00:30:22.781 --> 00:30:25.117
and his hair is wack. too.
which I also agree with.

587
00:30:25.200 --> 00:30:26.326
He's dead.

588
00:30:26.410 --> 00:30:27.995
-Why are you doing this to me?
-Last question.

589
00:30:28.495 --> 00:30:30.122
This one's for Jett.
You're in year fifteen.

590
00:30:30.205 --> 00:30:32.249
The team's bringing on a goat
to solve its problems.

591
00:30:32.332 --> 00:30:34.543
Do you ever wonder
if it's time to hang it up?

592
00:30:34.626 --> 00:30:36.837
I'm not hanging up anything. okay?

593
00:30:36.920 --> 00:30:39.798
I feel great right now. playing some
of the best ball of my career.

594
00:30:39.882 --> 00:30:42.968
And please. I've played with every mutt
this league has to offer.

595
00:30:43.051 --> 00:30:48.807
My only concern is going out there
and doing what I gotta do to win the Claw.

596
00:30:48.891 --> 00:30:52.477
and nothing. and I mean nothing.
is gonna get in the way of that.

597
00:30:52.561 --> 00:30:54.605
Thank you. Bagels on the third floor.

598
00:30:54.688 --> 00:30:55.731
Jett. over here!

599
00:30:55.814 --> 00:30:57.524
Yeah. Cool.

600
00:30:57.608 --> 00:30:59.693
-Will!
-Do you have any comment?

601
00:30:59.776 --> 00:31:01.778
I can-- Okay. thank you.

602
00:31:02.279 --> 00:31:03.530
Bye.

603
00:31:05.282 --> 00:31:09.077
Coach Dennis. how do you plan
on utilising the goat in the rotation?

604
00:31:09.161 --> 00:31:11.496
That's a great question. Well--

605
00:31:11.580 --> 00:31:13.582
Dennis. he's all yours.

606
00:31:13.665 --> 00:31:15.042
Hey. Jett. you got a second?

607
00:31:15.125 --> 00:31:17.794
I just wanted to go over these new plays.

608
00:31:18.921 --> 00:31:20.756
You heard me. We'll do it later.

609
00:31:21.798 --> 00:31:24.218
How you doing. kid?
Dennis Cooper. Pleased to meet you.

610
00:31:24.968 --> 00:31:27.638
I know you. Coach Dennis. It's an honour.

611
00:31:27.721 --> 00:31:29.515
Coach is a strong word.

612
00:31:29.598 --> 00:31:32.851
I'm more of an underpaid clipboard stand.

613
00:31:33.769 --> 00:31:35.145
But I keep trying.

614
00:31:35.229 --> 00:31:36.730
Let's get you suited up for the game.

615
00:31:36.813 --> 00:31:37.731
I'm ready to play.

616
00:31:37.814 --> 00:31:40.275
Play? I... That's cute. No.

617
00:31:40.359 --> 00:31:41.235
-What?
-Nothing.

618
00:31:42.110 --> 00:31:43.820
And here we are.

619
00:31:45.447 --> 00:31:48.408
No way. The Thorns locker room?

620
00:31:49.952 --> 00:31:51.245
Yes!

621
00:31:51.328 --> 00:31:53.789
Get dressed and come meet the team.

622
00:31:54.540 --> 00:31:56.667
Yes. yes. yes. yes!

623
00:31:56.750 --> 00:31:58.168
This is crazy!

624
00:32:01.255 --> 00:32:02.589
Yo!

625
00:32:03.382 --> 00:32:06.426
My name. On a Thorns jersey.

626
00:32:08.053 --> 00:32:11.014
Wait. Fillmore 13's?

627
00:32:21.733 --> 00:32:22.860
Not bad.

628
00:32:25.863 --> 00:32:26.905
Right?

629
00:32:30.409 --> 00:32:32.119
It's game night.

630
00:32:32.202 --> 00:32:35.914
Welcome back to
Regionally Organised Animal Roarball.

631
00:32:35.998 --> 00:32:38.292
The sport with the wildest courts.

632
00:32:38.375 --> 00:32:39.585
Stalactites.

633
00:32:39.668 --> 00:32:40.878
Sandstorms.

634
00:32:40.961 --> 00:32:41.795
Cliffs.

635
00:32:41.879 --> 00:32:42.754
Ice.

636
00:32:42.838 --> 00:32:44.548
Fire. And vines!

637
00:32:44.631 --> 00:32:46.466
Tonight. we're at the Greenhouse.

638
00:32:46.550 --> 00:32:48.385
and the stadium is rocking

639
00:32:48.468 --> 00:32:50.387
for the first
of three straight home games.

640
00:32:50.470 --> 00:32:55.184
And no surprise. the smalls have
shown up big for Vineland's newest Thorn.

641
00:32:59.688 --> 00:33:02.107
The Canoodle Cam is on patrol!

642
00:33:02.858 --> 00:33:04.776
Somebunny's in love!

643
00:33:04.860 --> 00:33:06.570
Looks like they're necking!

644
00:33:06.653 --> 00:33:09.323
"Polly want a cracker?"
Am I right. up-Chuck?

645
00:33:14.912 --> 00:33:15.913
You caught it!

646
00:33:17.164 --> 00:33:18.582
I'm a genius.

647
00:33:19.166 --> 00:33:21.752
Okay. Olivia. Clear your mind.

648
00:33:21.835 --> 00:33:23.170
I am in control.

649
00:33:23.253 --> 00:33:25.839
I know who I am. I am good enough.

650
00:33:25.923 --> 00:33:28.217
I do not care about
the opinions of others.

651
00:33:28.300 --> 00:33:31.053
I do not care what they're saying
about me online. right now.

652
00:33:31.136 --> 00:33:33.430
across multiple platforms
which I could check.

653
00:33:33.514 --> 00:33:34.806
just to see what they're saying.

654
00:33:34.890 --> 00:33:37.476
Phone! Phone. Does anyone have a phone?

655
00:33:37.559 --> 00:33:38.936
You're not even in uniform!

656
00:33:39.019 --> 00:33:40.979
Ha! It's tear-away.

657
00:33:41.063 --> 00:33:43.232
-Oh. Lenny.
-We're gonna get you!

658
00:33:44.107 --> 00:33:45.567
Daddy's a yeti!

659
00:33:45.651 --> 00:33:50.405
Listen. I celebrate your creativity
with the foam.

660
00:33:50.489 --> 00:33:54.952
but it's not okay to shoot Daddy
in the face. okay? Great.

661
00:33:56.078 --> 00:33:57.162
Cute kids.

662
00:33:57.246 --> 00:33:58.580
Yeah. I know. Right?

663
00:33:58.664 --> 00:34:01.667
Don't look now. but there's a baby goat
walking towards us

664
00:34:01.750 --> 00:34:04.127
with a weird smile on his face.

665
00:34:04.211 --> 00:34:05.712
I'm Will Harris.

666
00:34:05.796 --> 00:34:09.216
Ready to help the team win however I can.

667
00:34:09.800 --> 00:34:12.886
Look. a pre-game snack.

668
00:34:12.969 --> 00:34:15.639
Let me just unhinge my jaw.

669
00:34:15.722 --> 00:34:17.558
Please. please! No!
Don't eat me! Don't eat me!

670
00:34:17.641 --> 00:34:19.935
-It's the viral kid!
-He's sick?

671
00:34:20.018 --> 00:34:21.978
No. he went viral.

672
00:34:22.062 --> 00:34:26.483
Weird. I like it. Come. Dance.

673
00:34:26.567 --> 00:34:29.194
We're not doing your little dance. Modo.

674
00:34:29.277 --> 00:34:30.862
I kinda like it.

675
00:34:34.574 --> 00:34:37.202
What's with the egg?

676
00:34:39.161 --> 00:34:41.748
Don't let them control you.

677
00:34:43.792 --> 00:34:45.585
Roots run deep.

678
00:34:46.043 --> 00:34:47.754
Roots run deep.

679
00:34:47.838 --> 00:34:49.339
Roots run deep.

680
00:34:49.422 --> 00:34:51.675
It's really loud in here. right?

681
00:34:52.176 --> 00:34:55.512
Hey. Jett? Do you think I'll get
some playing time tonight?

682
00:34:56.972 --> 00:35:00.475
Introducing your newest Thorn.

683
00:35:01.185 --> 00:35:05.147
Coming in at a hot 5'7".

684
00:35:05.230 --> 00:35:06.940
from South Vineland.

685
00:35:07.024 --> 00:35:13.822
the Mane-slayer himself. Will Harris!

686
00:35:17.201 --> 00:35:18.410
Where'd he go? I can't see him.

687
00:35:18.493 --> 00:35:20.370
Will history be made tonight.

688
00:35:20.454 --> 00:35:23.373
or will he follow in
your underwhelming footsteps. Chuck?

689
00:35:23.457 --> 00:35:25.834
You suck. Rusty.
And yes. that was a bat joke.

690
00:35:25.918 --> 00:35:27.794
-Yeah! Let's go. Will!
-Yeah. Will!

691
00:35:27.878 --> 00:35:30.422
That's Will. right?
He kind of looks like a gerbil.

692
00:35:30.506 --> 00:35:32.257
Do you think Will's gonna play?

693
00:35:32.341 --> 00:35:34.843
I hope not. or we're gonna watch
that kid die on live TV.

694
00:35:34.927 --> 00:35:35.844
Gerald!

695
00:35:41.725 --> 00:35:44.645
-Great! Yes! There it is!
-Let's go. baby! Keep it up!

696
00:35:44.728 --> 00:35:46.480
Hey. Coach. when do you think
I might get in?

697
00:35:46.563 --> 00:35:50.734
-Just study the playbook. kid.
-End his bloodline!

698
00:35:50.817 --> 00:35:51.693
Story time?

699
00:35:51.777 --> 00:35:55.739
Yeah. Bring it in. Once. there was a play
called Eagle 24.

700
00:35:55.822 --> 00:35:57.407
I like this one.

701
00:35:57.491 --> 00:35:59.826
Anyone tired? I could sub in.

702
00:35:59.910 --> 00:36:01.119
-I could take a break.
-No.

703
00:36:01.870 --> 00:36:04.873
He's gonna be playing in the next game.
Trust me.

704
00:36:06.208 --> 00:36:07.334
We need a bucket here.

705
00:36:07.417 --> 00:36:10.212
Modo. hang out on the perimeter.
Space the floor.

706
00:36:10.295 --> 00:36:11.964
Do your thing.

707
00:36:12.047 --> 00:36:14.758
I always do.

708
00:36:15.676 --> 00:36:16.635
Ball! Ball!

709
00:36:16.718 --> 00:36:18.387
Ball! Ball! Ball! Ball!

710
00:36:18.470 --> 00:36:19.638
Ball! Ball!

711
00:36:20.848 --> 00:36:24.142
Hey. I actually noticed that the moose
always drives right.

712
00:36:24.226 --> 00:36:27.229
so if you just shift the defence a li--

713
00:36:27.312 --> 00:36:29.690
Who wants an acacia leaf break?

714
00:36:29.773 --> 00:36:30.899
I do!

715
00:36:33.610 --> 00:36:38.198
Tomorrow. history will be made.
and I mean it this time.

716
00:36:39.783 --> 00:36:40.993
Shake it off. Archie!

717
00:36:41.076 --> 00:36:44.413
-I got water. towels. emotional support.
-I'm covered.

718
00:36:44.496 --> 00:36:47.374
Three tough losses in a row
for the Vineland Thorns.

719
00:36:47.457 --> 00:36:52.045
And now they'll hit the road with a goat
who's yet to see a dime of playing time.

720
00:36:55.632 --> 00:36:57.009
Ouch.

721
00:37:08.729 --> 00:37:10.355
No days off. am I right?

722
00:37:10.439 --> 00:37:13.317
No. no. no. Nope.
This is a private practice session.

723
00:37:13.400 --> 00:37:16.320
Hey. watch this.
From the logo. Nothing but net.

724
00:37:19.489 --> 00:37:20.490
Lucky shot.

725
00:37:21.408 --> 00:37:23.202
Maybe. Bank shot.

726
00:37:24.703 --> 00:37:26.914
Should I play the lottery?
I'm feeling good today.

727
00:37:26.997 --> 00:37:28.749
Why are you here. kid?

728
00:37:28.832 --> 00:37:30.542
I want some playing time.

729
00:37:31.126 --> 00:37:32.252
Not happening.

730
00:37:32.336 --> 00:37:36.340
Let's shoot for it. Or are you scared
you're gonna lose to a goat?

731
00:37:38.300 --> 00:37:39.551
All right. Bet.

732
00:37:39.635 --> 00:37:42.262
Top of the stands.
hook shot off the glass.

733
00:37:42.346 --> 00:37:43.972
spin around the rim. in.

734
00:37:47.434 --> 00:37:49.394
Jett from downtown. Did it.

735
00:37:53.982 --> 00:37:55.317
Easy.

736
00:37:55.400 --> 00:37:57.027
Through the vines. in.

737
00:37:58.070 --> 00:37:59.404
Hot paws over here.

738
00:38:00.989 --> 00:38:02.366
Yeah. baby!

739
00:38:02.449 --> 00:38:03.450
What else you got?

740
00:38:03.534 --> 00:38:04.993
Off the top.

741
00:38:05.536 --> 00:38:06.578
in.

742
00:38:13.961 --> 00:38:15.337
Hanging from the lights.

743
00:38:16.547 --> 00:38:17.881
Easy.

744
00:38:24.179 --> 00:38:26.056
You are mine now.

745
00:38:28.517 --> 00:38:33.313
From the tunnel. over the backboard.
nothing but net. All right?

746
00:38:33.397 --> 00:38:37.651
If I hit this one.
you have to give me playing time.

747
00:38:38.443 --> 00:38:40.237
Okay. yeah. We'll see.

748
00:38:41.280 --> 00:38:42.281
Pack it up.

749
00:38:45.659 --> 00:38:46.660
You missed.

750
00:38:47.202 --> 00:38:50.289
Come on. we gotta fly. Plane leaves in 30.

751
00:39:01.758 --> 00:39:03.886
I really had to hustle back there. but...

752
00:39:03.969 --> 00:39:06.138
Yo! What?

753
00:39:06.221 --> 00:39:07.306
We're on a PJ?

754
00:39:09.725 --> 00:39:11.393
What? Sick.

755
00:39:11.476 --> 00:39:14.104
-Are you seeing this? Oh. no.
-You got dunked on!

756
00:39:14.188 --> 00:39:15.397
Are y'all playing Roar 2K?

757
00:39:15.480 --> 00:39:18.650
They've added memes?
I mean. why would they do that?

758
00:39:18.734 --> 00:39:20.110
It's so disrespectful!

759
00:39:20.194 --> 00:39:22.863
Not just to me. but to all birds.

760
00:39:22.946 --> 00:39:26.617
Auntie Olivia is not giving bird.
Birds fly.

761
00:39:26.700 --> 00:39:27.910
Are you broken?

762
00:39:27.993 --> 00:39:33.624
Hey. hey. Auntie Olivia has a condition
called flightless bird syndrome.

763
00:39:34.124 --> 00:39:36.752
Auntie Olivia can't fly.

764
00:39:36.835 --> 00:39:40.005
-But we can!
-Oh. no! Not the cockpit!

765
00:39:40.088 --> 00:39:41.173
Girls!

766
00:39:41.256 --> 00:39:44.343
-We're taking over this plane!
-Reporting for duty!

767
00:39:44.426 --> 00:39:46.762
-No. don't touch that!
-At least the bags are comfy.

768
00:39:46.845 --> 00:39:49.139
-Hey. Lenny. Is this seat taken?
-Yep.

769
00:39:49.223 --> 00:39:51.433
-By who?
-By me.

770
